sentence: The South Africa Medal (1880), often referred to as the Zulu War Medal, is a campaign medal instituted in 1880 and awarded by the British Government to members of the British Army, Royal Naval Brigade and Colonial Volunteers who were involved in a series of South African tribal wars in the Cape Colony, Colony of Natal and South African Republic between 1877 and 1879, most notably for the Anglo-Zulu War of 1879.
